headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook scored 23 points to become the 25th player in NBA history with 25,000 points, Kawhi Leonard had 21 of his 33 points in the first half and the Los Angeles Clippers put on an offensive show in a 136-125 win over the Detroit Pistons...
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook reaches 25,000 career points and Leonard scores 33 to lead Clippers past Pistons 136-125

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 24 points, Bam Adebayo added 20 points and 14 rebounds and the Miami Heat used a strong third quarter to earn a 110-102 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler, Adebayo help Heat outlast Wizards 110-102

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 32 points and 15 assists and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Phoenix Suns 129-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young posts 32 points, 15 assists as the Hawks beat the Suns 129-120

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 26 points and 12 rebounds to break Oscar Robertson’s single-season franchise record with his 30th consecutive double-double as the Sacramento Kings defeated the Indiana Pacers 133-122 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis breaks Robertson's franchise mark for consecutive double-doubles as Kings top Pacers 133-122

headlines.description: — Rookie Cam Whitmore scored a season-high 25 and Alperen Sengun had 24 points, 13 rebounds and eight assists in just three quarters to lead the Houston Rockets to a 135-106 rout of the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitmore has season-high 25, Sengun adds 24 as Houston Rockets rout Toronto Raptors 135-106

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga scored 29 points and the Golden State Warriors defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 121-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuminga scores 29 as the Warriors deal the Grizzlies their 4th straight loss, 121-101

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 23 points and six assists to help the Orlando Magic overcome a 17-point second-quarter deficit and beat the Minnesota...
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero's 23 points lead Magic in comeback from 17 down to defeat Timberwolves 108-106

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander is proving to be much more than one of the NBA's top scorers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander's 31 points lead the Thunder past the Hornets 126-106

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 33 points, including the winning layup over Victor Wembanyama and two other defenders with 3.8 seconds left, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the San Antonio Spurs 114-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson caps 33-point outing with winning layup as Pelicans overcome Spurs 114-113

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Whenever the Denver Nuggets start to take the floaters and volleyball-like tip passes from Nikola Jokic even a little bit for granted, they remember one thing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic posts 15th triple-double of season as Nuggets hold off short-handed Blazers 120-108
